=====================================
       ARC DATA GUIDE
=====================================


::KEY BINDINGS (may not be working)::
-------------------------------------
 [key {action}]              | set special keys for arc/dictionary
 {key [setting]}             | set special settings toggle keys
 (key (action/setting))      | set special hold keys


::MAP INTEGRATION::
-------------------------------------
 $imported map#              | needed map for arc (use import header)
 $generate map!              | needed map generated on-the-fly


::OPENING ARC::
-------------------------------------
 ***Starting Text***         | triggers at start; info/lore; arrows for multi-page (book animation)


::NON-STORY ELEMENTS::
-------------------------------------
 'monster name/type'         | monsters to spawn
 ~object name/type~          | expected drops
 drop%                       | drop percentage (follows monster/object or generic)
 +spawn_rates                | spawn percentage (follows monster/object or generic)


::INTERACTION SYSTEMS::
-------------------------------------
 ^interactable event^        | allowed events (exit trigger if no objects)
 *mandatory event*           | forced events (entry trigger if no objects)


::LOCATION SYSTEMS::
-------------------------------------
 @{LOCATION}                 | XY on map
 @{__LOCATION__}             | dynamic (__RANDOM__, __NEAR_WATER__, etc.)
 @{"SYMBOL"}                 | dynamic by symbol (e.g., @{"X"} for boss door)


::STORY ARC::
-------------------------------------
 /User's Thoughts/           | character's thinking text
 \User's Speech\             | character's speaking text
 _Noticed actions_           | description of events/observations
 -NPC Speech-                | NPC/NUPC speaking text
 ->'CHARACTER_NAME'          | address character (after thought/speech/action)
 ->data_phrase               | address via phrase (after thought/speech/action)


::CAUSE-&-EFFECT SYSTEMS::
-------------------------------------
 ANYTHING -> ANYTHING        | left happens -> do right (instant action)
 ANYTHING <- ANYTHING        | left waits for right (action block)
 <<                          | back effect: target after (may linger)
 >>                          | front effect: target before (may linger)


::EXIT ARC::
-------------------------------------
 ***Completion Text***       | on goal complete or arc end


::GOAL VALUES (up to 3 per arc)::
-------------------------------------
 Single (e.g., 1)            | goal order/position
 Double (e.g., 1;3)          | start goal; repeat count
 Triple (e.g., 1;2;3)        | sectional goals (gaps/sequences)


::NOTES::
-------------------------------------
- Use phrases/symbols for triggers (e.g., 'Q' home / 'I' instance for waypoints).
- Waypoints integrate with teleporters; instances connect to 1 (home/instance), homes to many instances.
- Speech around elements except listings; Event->object->text only non-goal determined text.
- Separate goals with ";" ; no space after goal value.

=====================================
  Build immersive stories with maps.
=====================================
